ia]] and [[Pakistan]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.radio.gov.pk/27-Oct-2016/indian-high-commission-s-official-declared-as-persona-non-grata|title=Indian High Commission's official declared as persona non grata|newspaper=Radio Pakistan|language=en-US|access-date=2016-10-27}}</ref> * On December 29, 2016, Thirty-five Russian diplomats were declared 'personae non gratae' by the United States in response to the alleged [[Russian interference in the 2016 United States elections|Kremlin-backed interference]] in the [[United States presidential election, 2016|2016 United States presidential election]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/12/29/obama-expels-35-russian-diplomats-election-hacking-row/|title=Barack Obama expels 35 Russian spies over election hacking row in 'Cold War deja vu'|newspaper=The Telegraph|access-date=2016-12-30}}</ref> * On March 4, 2017, the government of Malaysia declared the North Korean Ambassador to Malaysia, [[Kang Chol]], as persona non grata due to the murder case of [[Kim Jong-nam]] (the brother of [[Kim Jong-un]], [[List of leaders of North Korea|North Korean supreme leader]]) by [[VX (nerve agent)|VX nerve agent]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2017/03/03/malaysia-strongly-condemns-use-of-vx-nerve-agent-in-airport-murder/|title=Malaysia strongly condemns use of VX nerve agent in Jong-nam murder&nbsp;— Nation {{!}} The Star Online|website=www.thestar.com.my|access-date=2017-03-04}}</ref> Kang Chol was summoned by the ministry in [[Putrajaya]] but failed to appear just before the declaration & an apology was demanded by the Malaysian government due to accusations made by the North Korean ambassador for Malaysia.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2017/03/04/north-korean-ambassador-48-hours-to-leave/|title=N. Korean ambassador given 48 hours to leave&nbsp;— Nation {{!}} The Star Online|website=www.thestar.com.my|access-date=2017-03-04}}</ref> *In July 2017, the Venezuel