{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2018}} {{Use British English|date=February 2018}} {{for|the American book awards|Stonewall Book Award}} The '''Stonewall Awards''' was an annual event by [[Stonewall (charity)|Stonewall]] to recognize people who have affected the lives of [[United Kingdom|British]] lesbian, gay, bi and trans people. The event was first held in 2006 at the [[Royal Academy|Royal Academy of Arts]] and from 2007 was held at the [[Victoria and Albert Museum]]. It was held for the final time, with '...of the Decade' categories, in 2015.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Duffy|first1=Nick|title=Stonewall CEO explains why the Stonewall Awards are closing down|url=http://www.pinknews.co.uk/2015/10/15/stonewall-ceo-explains-why-the-stonewall-awards-are-closing-down/|website=PinkNews|accessdate=21 February 2017|date=15 October 2015}}</ref>
