{{refimprove|date=June 2018}} [[File:Cumhuriyet Halk Partisi Logo (2).svg|thumb|The Six Arrows]] The '''Six Arrows''' is the symbol and flag of the Turkish [[Republican People's Party (Turkey)|Republican People's Party]] (CHP). The arrows represent the fundamental pillars of [[Kemalism]], [[Turkey]]'s founding ideology. These are [[Kemalism#Republicanism|Republicanism]], [[Kemalism#Populism|Populism]], [[Kemalism#Nationalism|Nationalism]], [[Kemalism#Laicism|Laicism]], [[Kemalism#Statism|Statism]], and [[Kemalism#Reformism|Reformism]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=https://www.aydinlik.com.tr/alti-ok-anayasa-ya-nasil-eklendi-ozgurluk-meydani-subat-2018|title=Altı Ok Anayasa'ya nasıl eklendi?|last=Solak|first=Mustafa|date=2018-02-05|work=Aydınlık|access-date=2018-06-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180608003524/https://www.aydinlik.com.tr/alti-ok-anayasa-ya-nasil-eklendi-ozgurluk-meydani-subat-2018|archive-date=2018-06-08|language=tr}}</ref> The arrows are believed to have been conceived by {{ill|İsmail Hakkı Tonguç|tr}}.{{Citation needed|date=June 2018}} The principles of the Six Arrows were added to the [[Constitution of Turkey|Turkish Constitution]] in 1937.<ref name=":0" />
[[File:Gazi1933.jpg|thumb|200px|[[Mustafa Kemal Atatürk]] with the Six Arrows on his collar|right]]
